This paper discusses network neutrality and its impact on the Internet ecosystem, which is primarily related to computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also analyzes different scenarios of monopoly and competition, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the role of regulation and the concept of a Public Option ISP, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and communication and information theory (cs.CC).
